# Vue Reactivity & SFC

## Reactivity

- Keep source state minimal with `ref` / `reactive`
- Derive with `computed`; avoid recomputing expensive logic in templates
- Use `watch` / `watchEffect` only for side effects
- Do not duplicate derived values into extra refs

```ts
// ❌ BAD — derived state stored separately
const items = ref<Item[]>([])
const count = ref(0)
watch(items, (v) => { count.value = v.length })

// ✅ GOOD
const items = ref<Item[]>([])
const count = computed(() => items.value.length)
```

## SFC structure

Order sections: `<script>` → `<template>` → `<style>`.

- Keep SFCs focused; split large components
- Keep templates declarative; move branching/derivation into script
- Avoid `v-html` unless content is trusted/sanitized
- Always use stable `:key` on `v-for` lists (prefer ids over index)
- Prefer `v-if` for rare/expensive toggles; `v-show` for frequent toggles

## Performance (only after behavior works)

- Virtualize very large lists
- Consider `v-once` / `v-memo` for static or rarely changing subtrees
- Avoid heavy component abstraction inside hot list paths
